he form. Persuasive and perceptive, Rhetoric, Modality, Modernity is a novel rewriting of the history of rhetoric and a heady examination of the motives, issues, and flaws of contemporary inquiry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEnlightenment. 0aModality (Theory of knowledge). 0aPhilosophy, Modern. 0aRhetoric. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aphilosophy, rhetoric, truth, logic, speech, argument, persuasion, communication, inquiry, possibility, necessity, politics, hobbes, vico, modernity, walter benjamin, enlightenment, modality, epistemology, agency, plot, legal system, law, nonfiction, debate, political science, civic engagement, potential, determinism, capacity, positivism, aristotle, williams, peirce, hintikka, hegel, cicero.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022677748140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226777504423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226777504/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles